The paper proposes a hardware acceleration technique for deep neural networks using structured weight matrices. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the implementation of the technique on field programmable gate arrays (FPGAs) and application-specific integrated circuits (ASICs), which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction in computational complexity and storage complexity, which falls under the category of architecture (cs.AR).
